margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>        Elements essential to an understanding of
Christian freedom are diagrammed here in three sets of logical relationships: (1)
&lt;u>subjective&lt;/u> refers to our feelings about the matter; &lt;u>objective&lt;/u>
refers to what is there regardless of our feelings about it. (2) Plus (+) and
minus (-) mean the presence or absence of the category at the left for those
who are in Christ. (3)&lt;u> Jurisdiction of law&lt;/u> is divine regulation of human
behavior. &lt;u>Penalty of broken law&lt;/u> is the guilt consequence we have for
breaking God’s law. &lt;u>Reality&lt;/u> means the barriers, boundaries,
limitations—personal and external—in the reality where we live and what we are
a part of.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>STUDY GUIDE ON PRAYER</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-living/study-guides/study-guide-on-prayer/</link><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-living/study-guides/study-guide-on-prayer/</guid><description>&lt;style>
